      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "APOLLOSTORM (3) is back from a break of ten months and looks to be right up to the mark following a placing in a recent trial. Came from this barrier to kick off the last campaign with a win. Should enjoy an economical run so looks hard to beat on his return. ROCKNROLL WISH NZ (6) made it two from two this prep and four wins on the trot when he got the cash by a neck at Maryborough last time. Draws wide but won from this barrier first up at Bendigo. Has upside and winning form is hard to knock. THE GOLDEN HOOK (5) didn't do a bad job when beaten only 2.3 into fourth from the back line here last time out. GOOD DAY (2) draws well and is worth some thought based on his victory at Maryborough two runs ago.",
